cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.AI 

The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for optimization problems in wireless networks. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), neural networks (cs.NE), control systems (cs.SY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Given the focus on deep learning and optimization, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. However, the paper also discusses the specific constraints and challenges of wireless networks, which suggests that cs.IT and cs.SY are also relevant. The use of reinforcement learning and unsupervised learning further supports the inclusion of cs.NE and cs.AI as likely sub-categories.
